try, yielding low-abundance free ribose within a pentose mixture.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_005", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_007"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "Photochemical HCN homologation to formose ribose", "description": "HCN traps formaldehyde as glycolonitrile, which photochemically reduces to glycolaldehyde and then glyceraldehyde before entering borate-stabilized pentose production.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_006", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_016", "mol_006", "mol_007"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Direct borate-stabilized formose enrichment", "description": "Formose-generated glycolaldehyde and glyceraldehyde are funneled into a borate-stabilized and oxometalate-biased pentose pool in which ribose persists longer than under unmodified alkaline conditions.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_005", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_006", "mol_007"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Cyanosulfidic RAO capture and release", "description": "The strongest productive pathway avoids free ribose until the ribose aminooxazoline stage, then only secondarily releases free ribose under mild biochemical conditions.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_010"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_006", "mol_012", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Hybrid formose-to-RAO route", "description": "Formose supplies glyceraldehyde while cyanamide and phosphate trap glycolaldehyde into 2-aminooxazole, converging in ribose aminooxazoline before low-flux ribose release.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_005", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_010"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_006", "mol_007", "mol_012", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "name": "Glyoxylate-scenario route via ribulose", "description": "A clean ketosugar pathway generates ribulose from dihydroxyfumaric acid and glyceraldehyde, followed by limited ketose-aldose equilibration to ribose.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_011", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "name": "Phosphate-directed aldomerization route", "description": "Glycolaldehyde is phosphorylated and selectively aldomerized to ribose-2,4-bisphosphate, from which free ribose may be transiently liberated.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_015"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_018", "mol_019"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "name": "Formamide-assisted surface carbonyl entry to ribose", "description": "HCN is routed through formamide and back to formaldehyde-equivalent feedstock, then enters the formose/borate network to low-yield ribose.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_018", "rxn_019", "rxn_002", "rxn_005", "rxn_009"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_007"]}, {"pathway_id": "P9", "name": "Ribose stabilization-capture-release cycle", "description": "Free ribose formed in low abundance is captured as ribose 5-phosphate under borate-guided evaporative conditions and can re-enter the free ribose pool dynamically.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_009", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_014", "mol_020"]}, {"pathway_id": "P10", "name": "Hydrothermal-surface-phosphate composite route", "description": "Hydrothermal reduced carbon enters surface glycolaldehyde production, which is diverted into the phosphate-directed sugar-phosphate branch before speculative release of free ribose.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_015"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_018", "mol_019"]}], "hub_molecules": ["mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_007", "mol_012", "mol_014"], "convergence_points": [{"molecule_id": "mol_006", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_002", "rxn_004"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_013"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_007", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_005", "rxn_006"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_008", "rxn_009", "rxn_011"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_014"